a,Arial" SIZE=1>1</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5:53:20 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Questions Regarding Taunt</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ok I have heard some conflicting reports so I wanted to ask those who know. Should I use taunt everytime it pops up or would it have no effect  when the mob is on me and should I only press it once it turns to someone else?<br>
<br>
Also I am planning to make a macro for taunt. I will put taunt and disarm in there for sure. What I was wondering whether or not it is worth it to /sit on /sit off /attack on mid combat? The transition is very fast but do I lose more aggro from combat than I gain by sitting?<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks for all your help<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_icon.jpg height=30 width=30 BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>is a Formidable Opponent</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>140</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>11:32:03 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_portrait.jpg width = 136 height = 267 ></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Questions Regarding Taunt</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hehe might throw a /beg in there too or something.</font><P><center><IMG SRC="http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_nametag.jpg"></center><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2F2F4F><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uazalinofdarkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AzalinOfDarkon</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>knows that Warriors are Superior</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>1</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>12:59:58 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Questions Regarding Taunt</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">When fighting go ahead and taunt the mob everytime it comes up.  This still builds the skill, even when you solo.  Yes when you sit down your agro range does increase.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujaikarhalfelf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaikar HalfElf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Everybody's Favorite Hero</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>347</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2:40:49 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Community Supporter</FONT><BR><BR><img src=http://people.we.mediaone.net/nateman/Jaikar/jaikarphoto.jpg border=0></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><IMG SRC="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hit, not Sit</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ye only taunts when the foe be lookin' the other way! Otherwise, it won't be refreshed and ready ta go when ye REALLY needs it (cleric gettin' whacked on). Tauntin' anythin' that's already aggro'd on ye won't do nuthin' other than ta waste yer chance o' pullin' a creature offa yer huntin' partner later on.<br>
<br>
There ain't no preventive mainenance when it comes ta Tauntin'. Ye can't makes the foe hate ye any more if ye already gots it's attention -- yer either at the top o' the hate list or ye ain't. So's best thing ta do is hold off onna Tauntin' 'til the creature turns its head.<br>
<br>
If ye wants ta throw in Disarm and Beg and whutever else, fine...but sittin' down?! I dunno 'bouts that one. Ta stop attackin', sit down, stand up, then start attackin' again...no matter how fast ye does it, ye gots ta be losin' out on at least a coupla swings there. Now factor in how many times ye plan on Tauntin' in such a manner. Add it all up, and ye probably missed out on whut? 10? 20? 30? 40 swings o' yer blade? Now add in the crits, crips, procs, and damage that ye also missed out on...Then figure out how much less effective ye became as a tank each time yer foe whacked ye HARD while sittin' down (since we all know they seems ta hit harder when yer sittin' on yer arse)...Not ta mention how foolish ye'll look sittin' up and down...<br>
<br>
